content: {'id': 'ab774517-5e4e-3cc2-9dbe-ec8d8ec9d84c', 'contentType': 'STORY', 'title': "India's Godrej Consumer slumps 9% after flagging weak Q3 demand", 'description': '', 'summary': "(Reuters) -Shares of India's Godrej Consumer Products slumped 9% on Monday, set for their worst day since March 2020 and dragging down its peers in the fast moving consumer goods sector after the firm warned of stress on demand and profit margins in the third quarter.  Godrej Consumer said on Friday that two-thirds of its India business is under demand and margin stress due to higher raw material costs and unfavourable weather.  To partly offset higher costs in palm oil, a key ingredient for Godrej's soap business that contributes one-third to its standalone revenue, the company undertook measures including price increases during the quarter.", 'pubDate': '2024-12-09T06:46:46Z', 'displayTime': '2024-12-09T06:46:46Z', 'isHosted': True, 'bypassModal': False, 'previewUrl': None, 'thumbnail': None, 'provider': {'displayName': 'Reuters', 'url': 'https://www.reuters.com/'}, 'canonicalUrl': {'url': 'https://sg.finance.yahoo.com/news/indias-godrej-consumer-slumps-9-064646491.html', 'site': 'finance', 'region': 'SG', 'lang': 'en-SG'}, 'clickThroughUrl': {'url': 'https://finance.yahoo.com/news/indias-godrej-consumer-slumps-9-064646491.html', 'site': 'finance', 'region': 'US', 'lang': 'en-US'}, 'metadata': {'editorsPick': False}, 'finance': {'premiumFinance': {'isPremiumNews': False, 'isPremiumFreeNews': False}}, 'storyline': None}
